The paper discusses reinforcement learning algorithms and policy search methods for cooperative games, which are commonly studied in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions distributed policy search, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Additionally, the paper applies these methods to a simulated soccer domain, which is a common domain in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY).
